classAndMethodFor: aSymbol do: binaryBlock ifAbsent: absentBlock	"Looks up the selector aSymbol in this class/trait. If it is found, binaryBlock is evaluated	with this class/trait and the associated method. Otherwise absentBlock is evaluated.	Note that this implementation is very simple because PureBehavior does not know	about inheritance (cf. implementation in Behavior)"		^ binaryBlock value: self value: (self compiledMethodAt: aSymbol ifAbsent: [^ absentBlock value]).